					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/darkstuff" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1581620); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1581620&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252376" alt="DarkStuff" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1581620)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/darkstuff" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1581620); return false;" >DarkStuff</a></span> <span class="odate time_1575148882 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">30 Nov 2019 21:21</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4435441">
									

<p>It felt like it ended right before it was getting good &#8212; I wanted to see Chester and Blackwood's friendship get expanded! &#8212; but what is here is great. The animal representations of GoIs were clever (not that much thought had to go into the Serpent of the Serpent's Hand being a serpent, though the line &quot;I don't need to hear your stories, I know all stories&quot; was great), the tone was delightfully childish, and I liked the first Wondertainment actually being more <em>yellow</em> than <em>purple</em>, as the usual is the other way around. All around, simply great. Loved it. +1</p>
<p>Oh, and the art is super charming.</p>

